original_font_information.description: Fell Types -Double Pica size - Italic. Typeface from the  types bequeathed in 1686 to the University of Oxford by John Fell. Originally cut by Peter De Walpergen. Acquisition in 1684. To be printed at 21 points to match the original size. Autokerned using iKern developed by Igino Marini.
